  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How is Iphone 6s better than 6?",
  "response": "The **iPhone 6s** introduced several improvements over the **iPhone 6**, making it a more advanced and capable device. Here are the key differences:\n\n### 1. **3D Touch**\n   - The iPhone 6s introduced **3D Touch**, a pressure-sensitive display technology that allows for new interactions like \"Peek\" and \"Pop.\" The iPhone 6 lacks this feature.\n\n### 2. **Camera Upgrades**\n   - **Rear Camera:** The iPhone 6s has a 12 MP rear camera (up from 8 MP on the iPhone 6), offering better detail and higher-resolution photos.\n   - **Front Camera:** The front-facing camera was upgraded to 5 MP (from 1.2 MP on the iPhone 6), improving selfie quality and FaceTime calls.\n\n### 3. **Processor and Performance**\n   - The iPhone 6s is powered by the **A9 chip**, which is significantly faster and more energy-efficient than the A8 chip in the iPhone 6. This results in better performance for multitasking, gaming, and overall responsiveness.\n\n### 4. **RAM**\n   - The iPhone 6s has **2 GB of RAM**, compared to 1 GB in the iPhone 6. This allows for smoother multitasking and better app performance.\n\n### 5. **Touch ID**\n   - While both phones have a Touch ID fingerprint sensor, the iPhone 6s version is **twice as fast** as the one in the iPhone 6.\n\n### 6. **Build and Materials**\n   - The iPhone 6s uses **7000 Series aluminum**, making it stronger and more resistant to bending compared to the iPhone 6.\n\n### 7. **Operating System Support**\n   - The iPhone 6s supports newer versions of iOS for a longer period. For example, the iPhone 6s can run **iOS 15**, while the iPhone 6 is limited to **iOS 12**.\n\n### 8. **Live Photos**\n   - The iPhone 6s introduced **Live Photos**, which capture a few seconds of motion and sound before and after taking a photo. The iPhone 6 does not support this feature.\n\n### 9. **Color Options**\n   - The iPhone 6s added **Rose Gold** as a new color option, which was not available for the iPhone 6.\n\n### 10. **Storage Options**\n   - While both models started at 16 GB, the iPhone 6s was also available in higher storage capacities (up to 128 GB) during its release.\n\n### 11. **Battery Life**\n   - While battery capacities are similar, the A9 chip's efficiency in the iPhone 6s helps it maintain comparable battery life despite the increased performance.\n\n### 12. **Speed and Connectivity**\n   - The iPhone 6s supports faster LTE and Wi-Fi standards, improving download and upload speeds compared to the iPhone 6.\n\n### Conclusion:\nThe iPhone 6s is a significant upgrade over the iPhone 6, offering better performance, improved cameras, new features like 3D Touch and Live Photos, and enhanced durability. If you're choosing between the two, the iPhone 6s is the better option in almost every aspect.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
